> @tombburnell, works fine in the latest version: see [this CSB](https://codesandbox.io/s/late-violet-zz55ub?file=/src/App.tsx)

Hi, Your example doesn't contain an onChange()  handler on the input field.  If you add one like below, then the isDirty flag is not updated until the focus changes away from the edited field.
regards, Tom

function titleChange(e: any) {
    console.log("Title changed", e.target?.value);
 }
  
  return (
    <div>
      <Headers
        renderCount={renderCount}
        description="Performant, flexible and extensible forms with easy-to-use validation."
      />

      <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
        <input {...register("firstName")} placeholder="First Name" onChange={titleChange}/>
        <pre>
          <code>First Name: {firstName || "''"}</code>
        </pre>
        <button disabled={!isDirty} type="submit">
          Submit
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  );
